ğŸš€ Jenkins Docker CI Pipeline for MERN Application

This project demonstrates a real-world CI (Continuous Integration) pipeline using Jenkins and Docker for a MERN stack application.
The pipeline automatically builds Docker images for both frontend and backend services and pushes them to Docker Hub using secure credentials.

ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

In modern DevOps workflows, applications are packaged as Docker images and built automatically using CI pipelines.
This project shows how Jenkins can be used to:

Pull source code from GitHub

Build Docker images for a MERN application

Authenticate securely with Docker Hub

Push Docker images automatically

This pipeline focuses on CI only (build & push). Deployment is intentionally separated as a future step.

