âš™ï¸ Jenkins Pipeline Stages
1ï¸âƒ£ Checkout Source Code

Jenkins pulls the latest code from GitHub.

Reads the Jenkinsfile to execute pipeline steps.

2ï¸âƒ£ Build Backend Docker Image

Uses the backend Dockerfile

Builds the image:

thisandaprasanjana/backend:latest

3ï¸âƒ£ Build Frontend Docker Image

Uses a multi-stage Docker build

Builds the image:

thisandaprasanjana/frontend:latest

4ï¸âƒ£ Login to Docker Hub

Uses Jenkins credentials (username + access token)

Credentials are masked for security

5ï¸âƒ£ Push Images to Docker Hub

Pushes both images to Docker Hub automatically

ğŸ³ Docker Images

The pipeline publishes the following images:

Backend

thisandaprasanjana/backend:latest


Frontend

thisandaprasanjana/frontend:latest


Images are publicly available on Docker Hub and can be pulled from any machine.

â–¶ï¸ Run the Application (Optional)

You can run the images locally using Docker:

docker run -d -p 5000:5000 thisandaprasanjana/backend:latest
docker run -d -p 3000:80 thisandaprasanjana/frontend:latest


Or use Docker Compose (recommended for multi-container setup).

ğŸ” Security Practices

Docker Hub credentials are stored securely in Jenkins

Secrets are not hardcoded in the repository

Passwords are masked in Jenkins logs

